President Obama will award the 2015 National Medal of Arts and the National Humanities Medal to distinguished recipients on September 22, 2016. The National Endowment for the Arts and the National Endowment for the Humanities were established by Congress in 1965. The NEA has awarded over $5 billion to support artistic excellence and innovation, while the NEH has awarded $5 billion in grants to promote history, literature, philosophy, and language. The recipients of the National Medal of Arts include Mel Brooks, Sandra Cisneros, Morgan Freeman, Philip Glass, Berry Gordy, and more. The recipients of the National Humanities Medal include Rudolfo Anaya, José Andrés, Ron Chernow, Louise Glück, Terry Gross, and others. The event will celebrate the 50th anniversaries of both endowments.